=== 2.2 Dot Product

The *dot product* (also called inner product) of two vectors stem:[u, v \in \mathbb{R}^n] is a scalar:

stem:[u \cdot v = \sum_{i=1}^{n} u_i v_i = u_1 v_1 + u_2 v_2 + \ldots + u_n v_n]

Two key properties:

- *Geometric interpretation:* stem:[u \cdot v = \|u\| \|v\| \cos\theta], where stem:[\theta] is the angle between them.
  When stem:[u \cdot v = 0], the vectors are orthogonal (perpendicular).
- *Similarity measure:* if stem:[u] and stem:[v] are unit vectors, stem:[u \cdot v \in [-1, 1\]] is their cosine similarity.
  Attention scores in GPT are dot products between query and key vectors (Chapter 6).

