==== Example

Let stem:[u = [3, 4, 0\]] and stem:[v = [1, -2, 5\]]:

stem:[u \cdot v = (3)(1) + (4)(-2) + (0)(5) = 3 - 8 + 0 = -5]

Cosine similarity requires unit vectors.
stem:[\|u\| = \sqrt{9+16+0} = 5], so stem:[\hat{u} = [0.6, 0.8, 0\]].
stem:[\|v\| = \sqrt{1+4+25} = \sqrt{30}], so stem:[\hat{v} = [0.183, -0.365, 0.913\]].

stem:[\hat{u} \cdot \hat{v} = (0.6)(0.183) + (0.8)(-0.365) + 0 = 0.110 - 0.292 = -0.182]

The vectors point in moderately opposite directions.

